nodes.body:
> I think every bit0/bit1 pair should be replaced by an `ofNat` lemma

These already existed except for conj (though `map_*` also applies there). I'm not sure that makes sense for `I_{z,}pow`, but maybe I should restore those for $2n$ and $2n+1$ instead.
Can you change `ROrCLike` to `RCLike` in the comments?
Done, thanks

Thanks!

I think every bit0/bit1 pair should be replaced by an `ofNat` lemma
Can you add `conj_ofNat` to replace these?

```suggestion
-- replaced by `re_ofNat`
#noalign complex.bit0_re
#noalign complex.bit1_re
-- replaced by `im_ofNat`
#noalign complex.bit0_im
#noalign complex.bit1_im
```

```suggestion
-- replaced by `Complex.ofReal_ofNat`
#noalign complex.of_real_bit0
#noalign complex.of_real_bit1
```

```suggestion
-- replaced by `IsROrC.conj_ofNat`
#noalign is_R_or_C.conj_bit0
#noalign is_R_or_C.conj_bit1
```

```suggestion
-- replaced by `IsROrC.ofReal_ofNat`
#noalign is_R_or_C.of_real_bit0
#noalign is_R_or_C.of_real_bit1
```
Do we have analogs for these?
I think probably we should keep these, and any other lemmas about `pow`/`zpow` and `bit0`/`bit1`, for now. The rest of the patch is good to go modulo some comments.

```suggestion
-- replaced by `IsROrC.ofNat_re`
#noalign is_R_or_C.bit0_re
#noalign is_R_or_C.bit1_re
-- replaced by `IsROrC.ofNat_im`
#noalign is_R_or_C.bit0_im
#noalign is_R_or_C.bit1_im
```

Why disregard the align mechanism?
```suggestion
#align is_R_or_C.bit0_re RCLike.ofNat_re
#align is_R_or_C.bit1_re RCLike.ofNat_re
#align is_R_or_C.bit0_im RCLike.ofNat_im
#align is_R_or_C.bit1_im RCLike.ofNat_im
```
Same below
